properties.NAME: Levee - Midway
properties.DESCRIPTION: The Levee-Midway line connects Midway Substation in St. Lucie County to Levee Substation in Dade County via Corbett and Conservation Substations.
properties.COUNTIES: St. Lucie, Martin, Palm Beach, Broward, Dade
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Southeast District
South Florida Water Management District

properties.NAME: Crane - Bridge - Plumosus
properties.DESCRIPTION: This transmission line connects Crane substation to Plumosus Substation, through connections to Mapp, Hanson, Bridge, Moroso, Alexander, Steeplechase, Ryder, and Bonnette substations.
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Central and Southeast Districts
South Florida Water Management District

properties.NAME: Duval - Poinsett
properties.DESCRIPTION: These lines consist of two 500kV transmission lines from the Duval Substation in Duval County extending through the Rice Substation in Putnam County and the Rima Substation in Volusia County ending at the Poinsett Substation in Orange County.
properties.COUNTIES: Duval, Clay, Flagler, Putnam, Volusia, Orange, Seminole
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Northeast and Central Districts
St. Johns River Water Management District

properties.NAME: Bobwhite - Manatee
properties.DESCRIPTION: The transmission line connects from the Manatee Energy Center switchyard, within Manatee County, to the Bobwhite Substation located east of Interstate 75 in Sarasota County.
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Southwest and South Districts
Southwest Florida Water Management District

properties.NAME: Collier - Orange River
properties.DESCRIPTION: The line connects from the Orange River Substation in Lee County to the Collier Substation in Collier County.
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection South District
South Florida Water Management District

properties.NAME: St. Johns - Pellicer - Pringle
properties.DESCRIPTION: The line will connect the existing St. Johns Substation near St. Augustine in St. Johns County to the proposed Pringle Substation in the city of Palm Coast in Flagler County
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Northeast District
St. Johns River Water Management District

properties.NAME: Duval - Raven
properties.DESCRIPTION: The line begins at the existing Duval Substation in Duval County and terminates at the Raven Substation in Columbia County.
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Northeast District
St. Johns River Florida Water Management District and Suwanee River Water Management District

properties.NAME: Midway - Jensen - Crane
properties.DESCRIPTION: The line connects Midway Substation in St. Lucie County to Turnpike No. 3, an intermediate substation, also in St. Lucie County. From Turnpike No. 3 Substation the line will branch eastward to the Jensen Substation and southward to the Crane Substation.
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Southeast District
South Florida Water Management District

properties.NAME: DeBary - Winter Springs
properties.DESCRIPTION: The transmission line begins at the DeBary Power Plant in Volusia County, extends south to the FPL Tie Station and Sanford Plant through the Lake-Emma Substation, the North Longwood Substation, ending at the Winter Springs Substation in Seminole County.
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Central District,
St. Johns River Water Management District

properties.NAME: Central Florida - Kathleen
properties.DESCRIPTION: The transmission line begins at the Central Florida Substation and ends at the Kathleen Substation.
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Central and Southwest Districts,
Southwest Florida Water Management District

properties.NAME: Lake Agnes - Gifford
properties.DESCRIPTION: The line originates at Lake Agnes Substation in Polk County extends east, northeast through Osceola County along state road 429 ending at the Gifford Substation located in Orange County.
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Central and Southwest Districts
South Florida Water Management District

properties.NAME: Davis to Willow
properties.DESCRIPTION: Connects from the Davis Substation in Temple Terrace, Hillsborough County to the intermediate Wheeler Substation located along Wheeler Road northeast of Brandon in Hillsborough County and ends at the Willow Oak Substation west of Mulberry in Polk County.
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Southwest District
 Southwest &  South Water Management Districts

properties.NAME: Lake Agnes to Gifford
properties.DESCRIPTION: This transmission line begins at TECO's existing Lake Agnes Substation in Polk County to Duke Energy Florida's existing Gifford Substation in Orange County
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Southwest &  Central District
South Florida Water Management District

properties.NAME: Hopkins - Bainbridge Line
properties.DESCRIPTION: The City of Tallahassee constructed this transmission line from the Arvah B. Hopkins Generating Station to Georgia Power Cooperation's South Bainbridge Substation.
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Northwest District
Northwest Florida Water Management District

properties.NAME: Seminole - Keystone - Firestone (SECI)
properties.DESCRIPTION: This transmission line begins at SECI's Seminole Generating Station and connects to Clay Electric Cooperative's Riverview, Florahome, Keystone, and Black Creek Substations, ending at the JEA's Firestone Substation
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Northeast District
St. Johns River Water Management District

properties.NAME: Seminole - Keystone - Firestone (JEA)
properties.DESCRIPTION: This transmission line begins at SECI's Seminole Generating Station and connects to Clay Electric Cooperative's Riverview, Florahome, Keystone, and Black Creek Substations, ending at the JEA's Firestone Substation
properties.DISTRICTS:
Florida Department of Environmental Protection Northeast District
St. Johns River Water Management District
